How are you going to solve this problem?
As a simple citizen, I have worked to ensure that the travel guide remains a free trade, and this has been enforced.
The problem is small-minded politics - if someone comes from the right or from the left with a good proposal, it is deliberately rejected, and that only stops the population.
As an independent partyless person, I have much greater potential to gain support from all the parties represented in Parliament.
My advantage is that I can take what is best for our country from every party without any drawer thinking and party dogmas.
