From a Czech point of view, it seems to me that people see me more on the left.
But for me, this right-left thinking is completely irrelevant.
It's important to me that we move forward.
It's not about whether someone belongs to the left or to the right camp; I want to connect people.
I always publicly support any good solution, even if it comes from the KSČM or the ODS, and I will also oppose bad ideas.
You don't like anyone calling you a populist.
But don't you confirm that by what you just said?
If you set up a business plan in a company, you also have an ideal goal and a vision.
And you want to approach this.
